[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 4 890 863, with reports of cases by 217 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 98.3% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA, with more than 1.55 million confirmed cases, now represents 31.7% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 320 130 deaths have been reported, with 315 496 (98.6%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Russia is number 2, and Spain is number 3, followed by Brazil, the UK, Italy, France, Germany, Turkey, and Iran as number 10. China is now number 13. Russia has surpassed Spain and is now number 2 and Spain is number 3; Brazil is number 4, the UK has surpassed Italy and is 5; Italy is now number 6, France 7, Germany 8, Turkey 9, and Iran 10. The USA reported the highest number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (22 630) followed by Brazil (14 288), Russia (8926), India (4630), the UK (2711), Peru (2660), Saudi Arabia (2593), Mexico (2414), Iran (2294), and Chile (2278) reporting the 10th-highest 24-hour newly confirmed case numbers. - Mod.MPP]

