[4] China (Jilin): update on cases
A.
Date: Tue 19 May 2020 11:35:32 CST
Source: Xinhua News Agency [in Chinese, trans. Rapp.DS, edited]
http://www.jl.xinhuanet.com/2020-05/19/c_1126004374.htm


Jilin Province: 5 new confirmed local cases of novel coronavirus
----------------------------------------------------------------
Jilin Province Health Commission released the outbreak report on [19 May 2020]. For the 24-hour period on [18 May 2020], there was an increase of 2 confirmed local cases in Jilin Province (Jilin City). On [19 May 2020] midnight to 1 am, there was increase of 3 confirmed local cases in Jilin Province (Jilin City).

The 5 new cases are as follows:
- case 1: a close contact of confirmed case 3 reported by Jilin Province in Fengman District, Jilin City; residence is in Fengman District of Jilin City;
- case 2: a close contact of confirmed case reported by Jilin Province in Fengman District, Jilin City; residence is in Fengman District of Jilin City;
- case 3: a person returning from Shulan to Jilin; residence is in Jilin Hi-Tech Development Zone;
- case 4: a person returning from Shulan to Jilin, a close contact of reported confirmed case 3; residence in is Jilin Hi-Tech Development Zone;
- case 5: a close contact of confirmed case 3 in Shulan City reported by Jilin Province on [10 May 2020]; residence is in Shulan City.

As of [19 May 2020] at 1 am, Jjilin Province has reported a total of 132 confirmed local cases. 104 have recovered and been discharged from hospital. 26 patients are receiving medical care in isolation at hospitals (26 patients in Jilin City). 2 have died from illness. There are currently 3 patients in critical condition (Jilin City). The newly-added critical condition case had progressed from a normal case. There are now 1243 close contacts of confirmed local cases who are all in quarantine in designated locations undergoing medical observation.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Dan Silver

[The number of cases in Jilin continues to grow, with 5 newly confirmed cases in less than 24 hours -- involving 3 different locations: Fengman District Jilin City, Jilin Hi-Tech development zone, and Shulan City. A total of 132 local cases have been confirmed (but I do not know if this is the total since December 2019 or since 7 May 2020. - Mod.MPP]

----
B.
Date: Tue 19 May 2020 07:25:00 CST
Source: Jilin Provincial Government [in Chinese, trans. Rapp.DS, edited]
http://jl.gov.cn/zw/yw/zwlb/sz/202005/t20200519_7224067.html


On [18 May 2020] , Jilin Province held its 6th press conference for Jilin City epidemic prevention and control via video. The Assistant Secretary of Jilin Municipal Government, Yang Limin, introduced the latest status of epidemic prevention and control work in Jilin City and took related questions from reporters along with Changchun Medical University Vice President Leng Xiangyang and Jilin Municipal Health Commission Medical Affairs Medical Management Department Head Wang Bin.

Yang Limin reported the current status of the outbreak in Jilin City. In the 24-hour period on [17 May 2020], Jilin City had 2 new confirmed cases of which 1 case is in Shulan City and 1 case in Changyi District. Both are close contacts of previously-reported confirmed cases and were found and confirmed as part of proactive screening within the scope of prevention and control efforts.

To date, 9 patients have recovered and been discharged from hospital of which 1 was a case from outside China. Now, all 12 cross-border [imported, ex-China] confirmed patients who received medical care in hospitals have been discharged. The remaining 8 patients [discharged from hospital] were confirmed local cases. Of these, 4 were in Shulan City, 4 in Fengman District. Another 2 asymptomatic infections were quarantined for medical observation.

Since the 1st confirmed local case was reported in Shulan City on [7 May 2020], there have been a total of 34 confirmed local cases in Jilin City. Of these, 19 were in Shulan City, 12 in Fengman District, 2 in Chuanying District, 1 in Changyi District. There have been 2 asymptomatic infections. A total of 965 close contacts of confirmed local cases have been reported, of which 535 are in Shulan City. A total of 1692 secondary contacts of confirmed local cases have been reported, of which 832 are in Shulan City.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Dan Silver

[ProMED-mail would like to thank Dan Silver for finding and translating this article. It provides a nice glimpse into how the provincial government of a province bordering on one country with known major COVID-19 activity (Russia) and another country with speculated COVID-19 activity (North Korea) is handling importation and local transmission of the SARS-CoV-2. In total, there have been 34, locally acquired COVID-19 cases in Jilin since 7 May 2020; a sizeable number in an almost 2 week period. Other countries that are beginning to lift lockdowns, should see how this has been done in China, and learn from them. Especially with respect to testing all contacts, looking for asymptomatic infections that may well contribute to transmission of the virus to others unknowingly and should be in isolation. - Mod.MPP

Maps of China: http://www.chinatoday.com/city/MAP_0000.JPG and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7352326,155]

